			<h3 id="comments-title">
			One comment			</h3>

										<ol class="commentlist">	<li id="comment-398">
		<div  class="comment even thread-even depth-1 comment-wrap" >
			<div class="comment-avatar"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/905513c89c489bb171388a4dc9dde960?s=45&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D45&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-45 photo' height='45' width='45' /></div>
			<div class="author-comment">
				<cite class="fn">Lewis E. Kilgo</cite> 				<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.hangthebankers.com/the-matrix-of-power-hugo-salinas-price-multi-billionaire-from-mexico/#comment-398">	July 29, 2012 at 9:12 pm</a></div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->
			</div>
			<div class="clear"></div>
			<div class="comment-content">
									
				<p>A very enlightening article about the source of our current troubles. I have to disagree with the strict above/below duality view of power, however, especially in regards to the founding of the United States. The Founding Fathers, or &#8220;Elite&#8221; of the U.S. were men well educated in the values of the Enlightenment, which stood in opposition of power being used to promote the interests of one group at the expense of another. Most, if not all, of the founding fathers understood that Democracy was nothing more than a majority exercising tyranny over the remaining minorities in a society. This is why the U.S government was set up as a republic of states, with the members of those states electing representatives rather than voting directly on policy. The govenment in turn is supposed to be restrained by a fixed set of principles designed to discourage tyranny, which are embodied in the Constitution. All men being created equal does not mean equal intelligence or qualifiacetions for public office, but the equal rights to pursue their own interests so long as doing so does not infringe the rights of another to do the same. In short, the most basic founding principle is &#8220;No man is born to be a means to another man&#8217;s ends.&#8221; and the erosion of respect for that principle is the wellspring of our current troubles IMO. Our nation was not meant to be ruled &#8220;from above&#8221; or &#8220;from below&#8221;, but horizontally by a mutual understanding and respect for &#8220;self evident truths&#8221; or principles.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="reply"><a class='comment-reply-link' href='/the-matrix-of-power-hugo-salinas-price-multi-billionaire-from-mexico/?replytocom=398#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-398", "398", "respond", "5062")'>Reply</a></div><!-- .reply -->
		</div><!-- #comment-##  -->

	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol>
			    
							


